cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper proposes and evaluates deep neural network architectures for spatio-temporal prediction problems in Atari games, which involve high-dimensional frames and control variables. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and robotics (cs.RO). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories as the paper focuses on deep neural networks for video prediction.
